prompt:
Add a public function called CreateScores to Collections.calr that creates a dictionary mapping names to scores using §PUT and returns the count. The function takes no parameters and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor dictionary syntax:
§F{f001:CreateScores:pub}
  §O{i32}
  §DICT{scores:str:i32}
  §/DICT{scores}
  §PUT{scores} "Alice" 95
  §PUT{scores} "Bob" 87
  §PUT{scores} "Carol" 92
  §R §CNT{scores}
§/F{f001}

The dictionary syntax:
- §DICT{id:keytype:valuetype} §/DICT{id} creates an empty dictionary
- §PUT{id} key value adds or updates a key-value pair
- §CNT{id} returns the count of items
